@startuml Product_Browsing
title Product Browsing Flow

actor "Customer / Guest" as User
participant "Store Storefront\n(Next.js)" as UI
participant "Product Service\n(Spring Boot)" as PS
participant "Cache\n(Redis)" as Cache
participant "Product DB\n(PostgreSQL)" as DB

== Load Store & Categories ==

User -> UI : Open store page\n(store.flowmerce.com)
UI -> PS : GET /stores/slug/{slug}
PS -> Cache : Check store data in cache
Cache --> PS : Cache HIT → return store info

UI -> PS : GET /categories/{storeId}
PS -> Cache : Check categories in cache

alt Cache HIT
    Cache --> PS : Return categories
else Cache MISS
    PS -> DB : Query categories by storeId
    DB --> PS : Return categories
    PS -> Cache : Store in cache
end

PS --> UI : Store info + categories
UI --> User : Render store homepage\nwith category navigation

== Browse & Filter Products ==

User -> UI : Apply filters\n(category, price range,\nin-stock, sort order)
UI -> PS : GET /stores/{storeId}/products/public\n?category=X&minPrice=Y\n&maxPrice=Z&inStock=true\n&sort=price_asc

PS -> Cache : Check cache for\nthis exact query key

alt Cache HIT
    Cache --> PS : Return cached results
else Cache MISS
    PS -> DB : Query products with filters\n+ pagination
    DB --> PS : Return matching products
    PS -> Cache : Cache results\n(short TTL ~60s)
end

PS --> UI : Paginated product list\n{products, totalCount, page}
UI --> User : Display product grid\nwith prices, images, stock badges

== Search by Name ==

User -> UI : Type in search bar
UI -> PS : GET /stores/{storeId}/products/search\n?keyword=value
PS -> DB : Full-text search query
DB --> PS : Return matching products
PS --> UI : Search results
UI --> User : Display filtered results

== View Product Details ==

User -> UI : Click on a product
UI -> PS : GET /stores/{storeId}/products/{productId}
PS -> Cache : Check product detail cache

alt Cache HIT
    Cache --> PS : Return product detail
else Cache MISS
    PS -> DB : Query product by ID\n(name, description, images,\nprice, stock, category)
    DB --> PS : Return product detail
    PS -> Cache : Cache product detail
end

PS --> UI : Full product details
UI --> User : Render product detail page\n(images, description, price,\nstock status, add to cart)

@enduml
